A crack is an execution application that works around or has a password as a part of it (at least my interpretation).  What you have to do is find the execution on the one of the mdf files by (this is what I use) mounting it on daemon tools (free software) then browsing the virtual drive you mounted it on (you can check which drive you mounted it on because it tells you Device *some number: [the drive] then what you have mounted on it).  In that drive you explore, it (the game directory) should have another execution (the cracked one).  You copy that execution (in the game directory you are exploring) and past it on the execution application in the program files for the game (the applications SHOULD have the same name).  now when you try to play it should work.
